Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 1
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by lamellar ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 2
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by fine scales on the scalp

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 3
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by mild ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 4A
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by generalized ichthyosis and ectropion that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound hetrezogyous mutation in the ABCA12 gene on chromosome 2q35.

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 4B
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by severe neonatal ichthyosis with bilateral ectropion and eclabium

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 5
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by fine white or greyish-white scales
Synonym: autosomal recessive congenital nonlamellar and nonerythrodermic ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 6
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by generalized ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 7
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by fine whitish scales

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 8
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by diffuse lamellar ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 9
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by fine erythrodermic scales

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 10
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by generalized ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 11
Definition: An autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis characterized by ichthyosis

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 13
Definition: A Meier-Gorlin syndrome that has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the MCM5 gene on chromosome 22q12.

Name: autosomal recessive congenital ichthyosis 14
Definition: A Meier-Gorlin syndrome that has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the MCM5 gene on chromosome 22q12.
